fields.title: Prisoners
fields.review: The movie offers some slick foreboding, crafty twists, and a satisfying ending.

fields.title: Ready or Not
fields.review: The movie is wildly entertaining, crackles with energy, and never letting your attention waiver.

fields.title: The Invitation
fields.review: Despite a very likable lead and a refreshingly light touch, the movie is ultimately too predictable to thrill as either a romance or a horror story.

fields.title: A Simple Favor
fields.review: This movie got strands of DNA from 'Gone Girl'. A Simple Favor is an intriguing, darkly comic thriller that keeps things moving at a well-paced clip and never lets the plot get ahead of itself.

fields.title: I Care A Lot
fields.review: Rosamund Pike is almost too effective, her delicious villainy too irresistible to completely loathe. From her sharp canary yellow suit to her fearless resolve, Marla may be problematic, but she is fabulous.

fields.title: Red Notice
fields.review: To me, this movie is just some good dumb fun.

fields.title: Murder on The Orient Express
fields.review: What remains most pleasurable about this movie is the stylish and classical quality of the storytelling; it's an old-fashioned sort of murder mystery in more than the obvious ways.

fields.title: Bullet Train
fields.review: This movie certainly serves the Brad Pitt brand, but it's too weak to deliver him to a new destination.

fields.title: Work It
fields.review: As a dance movie, Work It moves just fine.

fields.title: The Babysitter
fields.review: This movie is just fun. The Babysitter exploits its elements with such wit that even with its cliches, it never manages to be boring.
